				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here are my semi-final results..I might do one more set of parsing's just to help reduce the variance, but not sure yet.  It takes a lot of time.
<br />

<br />
/pet hold would probably make doing these tests easier and more accurate due to longer sampling sessions.
<br />

<br />
Target Mob: Bloodmaw in GD
<br />
Fight Duration Per Test: ~13 minutes.
<br />

<br />
*Full Armor = Plate + 2 x Lev rings + Ele Defender ( Raw AC = +94 )
<br />

<br />
Interesting item here is the 59 Air Pet results...it appears that armor'ing it might be worth less then it is for the 57 Earth Pet.
<br />

<br />
Also worth noting that the Pet's aviodance generally got worse with armor..almost like it got encumbered.  The 49 Earthpet was hit the worst with that effect, while 57 and 59 pets differences could go away with a larger sample size.  Hard to say.
<br />

<br />
Taken from a study on my guild board done shortly after the great monk mitigation nerf.
<br />

<br />
MC = Mitigation coefficient as (avg-min)/(max - min) ie: 0 is good! 1 is bad!
<br />
** Player MC was calculated by letting mob hit the player with player's back facing the mob.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">
<br />
Pet&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Focus&nbsp; &nbsp;Buffs&nbsp; &nbsp;Gear&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Avoidance%&nbsp; &nbsp;Avg Hit&nbsp; MC
<br />
49 EarthYes&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;BO3&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;None&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 41.5&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;52&nbsp; &nbsp;0.588
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Yes&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;BO3&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Full&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 34.5&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;45&nbsp; &nbsp;0.485
<br />
