			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't think there was ever any question that L65 characters could mitigate better than L41, L45, and L48 pets.
<br />

<br />
The 61-65 (pet L60) pets are a world apart from 49-59 (pet L41-L48), as far as tanking ability goes.  Also, the lack of mitigation differences with the L65 characters suggests a test "attackee" with a very low attack rating relative to the ACs of those characters.  Every class' mitigation approaches the same value at the "low end" of atk/def, as it does at the "high end" atk/def matchups.  As an example, an atk of 5000 from a mob over defs of 900-1200 is so overpowering that every def subject will take near the same damage.  likewise, an atk of 200 vs a def of 900-1200 is so underwhelming, the values again approach the same value.
<br />

<br />
If you're going to make damage mitigation comparisons between such large level gaps, I think any conclusion you could come to is pretty much moot.  This would be a real interesting study if it involved L50 player characters and the older pets, or PoP pets and the L65 characters.
<br />

<br />

<br />
The differences in avoidance and mitigation from armoring a pet are also interesting, but you need a much larger sample to say something as drastic as "armoring pets encumbers them and lowers their avoidance".
<br />

<br />
If the epic is included in such a test, remember that the Epic is the one pet than you cannot armor with anything other than jewelry (and not bracers).  This is because the Epic pet comes equipped with a full set of armor (equiv to Phantom Chain) to begin with, and NPCs will not equip armor into a slot they already have gear in.  
<br />

<br />
Weapons are a different story -- they will replace a high delay weapon with a lower delay one.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Arhallia Ironborne</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: blue"><span style="font-weight: bold">Alliance of the Arcane</span></span>
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Quellious server</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
