			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Arhallia: Test your 65th lvl pets and post the results.  
<br />

<br />
It would be <span style="font-weight: bold">very</span> interesting to see how a lvl 65 mage's pet compares to a lvl 65 player character and the lower level pets against the same test dummy.  The progression of pet defensive power in relation to pet and PC levels could provide a good basis for mage pet improvments.  I really don't like the fact that a 56th lvl shaman can mitigate dmg better then a 59th lvl mage pet.  If a 56th lvl shaman can mitigate better then a 65th lvl pet...then that's even worse.
<br />

<br />
A few mages have been asking for pets to have 10K HP.
<br />
A few mages have been asking for bigger heals to go along with those 10K.
<br />
A few mages have been asking for a pet that can off tank a mob.
<br />
The pet canni nerf hurt more then just the 65th lvl mages.
<br />

<br />
Knowing where you are is the best way to get to where you wanna be.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">This is because the Epic pet comes equipped with a full set of armor (equiv to Phantom Chain) to begin with, and NPCs will not equip armor into a slot they already have gear in. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Might be true, might not.  Based on Kirium's "test results", I'd have to disagree with that "commonly" held belief.  Look at the MC numbers for the pets in his parsing results...the Non Armored Epic did much worse then the Armored Epic Pet. Those results come very close to matching against both mobs too.  Take your epic pet to bloodmaw in GD, /pet hold it parse the results.  Try giving it armor and parse those results too.  If the numbers don't come close to matching, then "everyone's" belief that epics don't use summoned plate armor can be debunked.<br />_________________<br />Verser - 65th .49999 Elf Bard
<br />
Sleethr - 61st Dark Elf Mage
<br />
Medec - 61st Dorf Battle Cleric
<br />
Bertoxxolus: Order of the Scattered Winds</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
