			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>akherat wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I may have gotten the terms mixed up, but hopefully the point is still being made:
<br />

<br />
pets get hit harder less often without armor, but get hit more often for less with armor.  This indicates they are receiving the positive benefits of a higher ac, but those benefits are being offset by the lowered avoidance.  This should not be the case.
<br />

<br />
the mitigation and avoidance abilities of pets compared to PC's is significantly worse, even though the pets should have roughly similar stats and AC.
<br />

<br />
so long story short:
<br />

<br />
1.  The armor meant to help pets isn't helping, it's hurting.
<br />

<br />
2.  Pets are taking too much damage, irregardless of the armor.
<br />

<br />
At least that's what I'm hoping SOE will take away from this.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I have not parsed the pets, but from my own experience I know this is not true for the 53rd Air Pet, the 54th Water Pet, and the 57th Earth Pet. 
<br />

<br />
I soloed Slixn whatever in Burining Woods for the Dirt of the Underfoot piece for our epic.  You could use 3 chainned 51st earth pets or one fully equiped 53rd airpet alternating nukes/heals.  If you foolish forgot to equip your air pet, it only got Slixn to about 50% HP before it died. 
<br />

<br />
I soloed 18 AA's off the Dryads in Jagged Pine.   Most of them using the 53rd Air Pet.  With a fully buffed air pet I could take a cycle of 6 spawns, 7 if I got lucky and no wandering animal added.  If for some reason, I forgot to equip the pet, I could only take a cycle of 5 spawns.  I was always able to figure out I forgot to equip the pet because it was taking too much damage and I would have to skip a spawn to let the pet regen and I would have to heal it.   It would only take a couple of spawn cycles to make it completely obvious.  
<br />

<br />
I got 12 AA's at 55 from the dryads.  I was looking for the most efficent way to kill them.  I tried both a fully equipped water pet and a base water pet mixed with pet canni as well as the fully equipped air pet.  The water pet killed the mob much faster than the air, but it took more damage as well.  Against just the dryads, it was fine, but if a animal wander added, it was about 50-50 wheter it could tank both or end up dying.  Since a couple of trips to the zone line or a unrezzed death really lowered the efficency of the camp.  I then moved on to a fully equipped water pet.  It could then tank a dryad and a single animal wander add all the time without dying.  
<br />

<br />
I was two boxing my cleric and using my DDD pet in the gnoll caves when I dinged 57th.  Just to test out the new earth pet, I spent a couple of sessions in the caves as well.  Again, I tested it with and without being equipped.  While giving it armor did it help, it was not nearly as a profound effect as with the DDD.  But it did definately help.  What is interesting about the 57th earth pet was giving it equipment or buffing it with my cleric made little difference in how much damage it took.  However, doing both did reduce the damage it was taking.  It seems that increasing the Earth's pet AC just that much more, really increased its damage mitigation, at least against the gnolls I were fighting. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
