			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Last night I did a few more pet mitigation/tanking tests.
<br />

<br />
Seeing as I've seen many posts saying that our pets cannot tank Tier 2+ PoP mobs off I go to PoValor looking for something to test on.
<br />

<br />
Not been sure if I could keep pet alive just using mage heals this test was done against Planarian Larvae, Lvl 59/60 mobs (I asked a Lvl 59 PC what they conned and was told white or yellow though I suspect they were all lvl 59).
<br />

<br />
Max hit from these mobs was 434, min hit 94, a fair step up from the 329 max hitting Wraiths from PoN.
<br />

<br />
Pet used was a SoAS focussed Air pet with every available piece of armour I could summon for it (plate suit minus bracers, 2 focus bracers,r ings, earrings, focus shawl and neck, elemental defender for backslot). This added 129 ac (24 more than in the PoN tests).
<br />

<br />
I pulled each mob with Malosinia (recast if needed until it landed) and just let pet (with DS) tank it down. I did land 1 Sun Vortex on each mob when it was low to ensure I got full XP (to test XP gain from these mobs).
<br />

<br />
Averaged over 5 mobs (381 hits) following results obtained:
<br />

<br />
Mob Accuracy: 58.7%
<br />
Mob Delay: 27
<br />
Mob mean hit: 263
<br />
DPS taken by pet: 99.2
<br />

<br />
It was pretty easy to keep the pet alive using just PR against these mobs, I rarely had to use TER and never had to use Mend Companion.
<br />

<br />
Whilst the test is pretty short if you look at each individual fight the spread of the DPS taken is remarkably consistent ranging from 92 to 106. This is something I have always seen, that there are not huge swings in damage taken from mob to mob.
<br />

<br />
Are these mobs good for XP gain? Then no, they suck bad despite been Lvl 59 mobs. The 5 kills only gained me 11% aa, this compared badly to (IIRC) 13% gained from 7 Blood Raven kills. A Blood Raven does nearly half the dps to the pet and can be killed in about 60% of the time it takes to kill a Larvae.  It is far more efficient to kill Blood Ravens than Planarian Larvae, even though the larvae are the fabled Tier 2 mobs.
<br />

<br />
My next aim is to test against mobs that max hit for 500'ish and ones that are 60+ as I suspect thats where you start seeing the XP bonus for Lvl 65 characters.
<br />

<br />
Edit: Just worked out Sleethr's Mitigation Coefficient for this parse and get 0.479. 4% lower than the other 2 parses for Armoured Air pet. Is this extra 4% due to the higher AC I added for the Planarian Larvae test? If so then getting a Virtue for the pet should provide significant gains over the fully armoured pets in terms of how much dps they take.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
